Jenkins Server setup:
======================
1.install jenkins from jenkins setup : https://github.com/Brahmamk3/DevOps-Documents/blob/main/01-Jenkins-Server-Setup.md
2.install docker from Jenkins-Docker-K8S.md--step-6: https://github.com/Brahmamk3/DevOps-Documents/blob/main/10-Jenkins-Docker-K8S.md
3.install maven : sudo apt install maven -y
in jenkins:
===========
installed plugins: 
1.Docker Pipeline
2.pipeline:stage view
3.ssh agent

credentials:
1.dockerhub credentials L username and password
2.minikube-shh credentials : ssh with private key

dockerfile and piplescript and deployment-service.yml(for normal not helm) same.
jenkinsfile pipeline script for normal 
jenkinsfilehelm foe helm type question

Minikube server setup:
==========================
1. Install minikube form minikube setup : https://github.com/Brahmamk3/DevOps-Documents/blob/main/13_MiniKube_Setup.md
2. Install helm if needed : 
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/master/scripts/get-helm-3 | bash
helm version
helm create mycart
cd mycart/
vim values.yml
image:
  repository: brahmamk015/demo-repo
  tag: "springboot5"
service:
  type: NodePort
  port: 8080
  targetPort: 8080
  kubectl port-forward --address 0.0.0.0 service/springboot-service 8080:8080
  http://minikube-ed2-public-ip:8080/addressbook/


  suggestions:
  1.values.yml:
   image:
     repository: brahmamk015/demo-repo
     tag: "springboot5"
   service:
     type: NodePort   # Good! Needed for external access
     port: 8080
     
⚠️ Don’t forget to also set `targetPort: 8080` in your service section. 

2.Access from browser:
   http://<Minikube-EC2-Public-IP>:<NodePort>/addressbook/
